  <h2>Simple Setup</h2>

  <p>
    First, copy the <code>codebase/</code> folder (containing the <code>css/</code>, <code>js/</code> and <code>scss/</code> folders) into your project.
  </p>

  <p>
    Example simple HTML to get started:
  </p>

  <pre><code class="language-none">&lt;!doctype html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset="utf-8"&gt;
    &lt;meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge,chrome=1"&gt;
    &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Your Webpage Title&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to/codebase/css/codebase.css"&gt;
    &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to/your-theme/css/styles.css"&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;

    &lt;!-- Get to work --&gt;

    &lt;script src="path/to/jquery.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script src="path/to/codebase/js/codebase.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script&gt;
      $(document).codebase();
    &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script src="path/to/your-theme/js/scripts.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>
    Note that jQuery needs to be sourced first, so that the Codebase jQuery scrips can work.
  </p>

  <h2>Advanced Setup</h2>

  <h3>(1.) SCSS</h3>

  <p>
    After copying in the <code>codebase/</code> folder as above, build your project theme structure, e.g.:
  </p>

  <pre><code>codebase/
  ├── css/
  ├── js/
  └── scss/

theme/
  ├── css/
  ├── js/
  └── scss/</code></pre>

  <p>
    You can import Codebase into your project base SCSS file. But before you do that, you may wish to override any/all of the SCSS variables in Codebase. This can easily be done because they are all set as <code>!default</code> variables. To override them, declare or import your overrides (i.e. variables with the same names but your preferred values) <b>before</b> importing Codebase.
  </p>

  <p>
    So for example, if you have copied the Codebase folder as a sibling folder beside your project theme folder (as I have done for this documentation 'theme'), then you can set up as follows:
  </p>


  <pre><code>// YOUR PROJECT BASE SCSS FILE
// ===========================

// Your overrides of Codebase !default variables

...

@import '../../codebase/scss/codebase';

// Your project

...</code></pre>

  <h3>(2.) JS / jQuery</h3>

  <p>
    The Codebase jQuery script is a set of (<code>cb_</code>-prefixed) plugins &ndash; each of which you can call &ndash; and a "master" (document ready setup) plugin <code>codebase();</code> that is called by...
  </p>

  <pre><code>$(document).codebase();</code></pre>

  <p>
    ...on the last line of <code>codebase/js/codebase.js</code>.
  </p>

  <p>
    If instead you wish to call <code>codebase()</code> from within your own theme/app jQuery script or you wish to create your own master function (or plugin), then simply comment out the <code>$(document)</code> call.
  </p>

